  <p class='header1'>Sources</p>
  <p><b>A. Legislation</b>
<p><b></b>
<p>The main source for legislation is the <b>Official Gazette of the Republic of Cyprus</b> (Επίσημος Εφημερίς της Δημοκρατίας) which has been published since Independence (16.8.1960). The House of Representatives of the Republic also publishes the Minutes of its Plenary Meetings since Independence (16.8.1960). The most updated website concerning Cypriot legislation is <a href="http://www.leginet.eu/">www.leginet.eu</a>
<p>The <b>Constitution of Cyprus</b>, as well as the Treaty of Establishment, the Treaty of Guarantee, the Treaty of Alliance and other important legal documents concerning Independence may be found in English in <i>Cyprus, Presented to Parliament by the Secretary of State for the Colonies, the Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs and the Minister of Defence by Command of her Majesty</i>, Command 1093, London, Her Majesty’s Stationery Office, 1960. The original text of the Constitution has been published separately in Greek and Turkish. 
<p>The most complete collection of Legislation since Independence was published in 15 volumes by Κορακίδης Επαμεινώνδας, Κορακίδου Μαρία, <i>Νόμοι</i><i> </i><i>της</i><i> </i><i>Κυπριακής</i><i> </i><i>Δημοκρατίας</i>, Πάφος 1998-2001.
<p>A comprehensive collection of some of the most important laws of the Republic were collected in Ανδρέας Νεοκλέους &amp; Σία ΔΕΠΕ, <i>Εγκόλπιο</i><i> </i><i>Κυπριακών</i><i> </i><i>Νόμων</i>, Νομική Βιβλιοθήκη, Αθήνα, 2008, σσ. 1231. 
<p>The Republic of Cyprus has officially published its Subsidiary Legislation since Independence in 2002 (Κυπριακή Δημοκρατία, <i>Διαδικαστικοί</i><i> </i><i>Κανονισμοί</i><i> 1960 – 2001</i>, Λευκωσία, 2002). 
<p>The Constitution of Cyprus has been published in Greek and English and translated into demotic Greek by Αδαμίδης Μάριος, <i>Σύνταγμα</i><i> </i><i>της</i><i> </i><i>Δημοκρατίας</i><i> </i><i>της</i><i> </i><i>Κύπρου</i>, Λευκωσία, 2004. The 1960 Treaties have been published by Macris D. Nicolas, <i>The 1960 Treaties on Cyprus and Selected Subsequent Acts</i>, Mannheim: Bibliopolis, 2003. 
<p>With respect to legal documents of the constitutional history of Cyprus and the Cyprus Problem the following publications may be consulted: 
<ul>
<li>Ιωάννου Ξ. Μίκης, <i>Το Κυπριακό μέσα από Νομικά Έγγραφα και τα Ψηφίσματα του ΟΗΕ (1960 – 1990)</i>, Λευκωσία, 1991.</li>
<li>Καραμπαρμπούνης Λ. Χάρης, <i>Κύπρος: Από την Εισβολή στην Ένταξη</i>, Εκδόσεις Α. Σάκκουλα, Αθήνα, 2003. </li>
<li>Παπαδόπουλος Λεωνίδας, <i>Το Κυπριακό Ζήτημα: Κείμενα 1959 - 1974</i>, University Studio Press, Θεσσαλονίκη, 1999. </li>
<li>Hakki Metin Murat, Cyprus: <i>Select Treaties and Documents</i>, Tauris, London, 2004, v. I-II. </li>
<li>Soulioti Stella, <i>Fettered Independence: Cyprus 1878-1964</i>, Modern Greek Studies/University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, 2006, v. II. </li></ul>
<p>There have been various official publications of specific legislations by the Press and Information Office of the Republic of Cyprus, as well as unofficial publications (e.g. by Antoniou Press). The following publications contain collections of specific Cypriot legislation after Independence: 
