<p>The <b>Cyprus Gazette</b> was published from 1878 until 11.8.1960 and contained legislation enacted during the British Rule of Cyprus. The Laws of Cyprus in force on 1<sup>st</sup> April 1959, before Independence, were compiled by then Attorney-General Criton Tornaritis and are separated into six volumes and Chapters (Caps). Laws who continue to be in force after Independence are referred to by their respective Cap in the 1959 edition (e.g. Interpretation Law is Cap. 1, Advocates Law is Cap. 2 etc.). 
<p><b></b>
