<li>Josephides Julius, <i>Subsidiary Legislation of Cyprus: Rules of Court, Orders of her Majesty in Council and other Public Instruments Affecting Courts and Tribunals in Force on the 31<sup>st</sup> December 1953</i>, Nicosia, 1953, v. II. </li></ul>
<p>Palaiologos had published an Index of Legislation before Independence in Παλαιολόγος Κ. Α, <i>Κλεις</i><i> </i><i>της</i><i> </i><i>Κυπριακής</i><i> </i><i>Νομοθεσίας</i><i> </i><i>από</i><i> </i><i>της</i><i> </i><i>Αγγλικής</i><i> </i><i>Κατοχής</i><i> </i><i>μέχρι</i><i> </i><i>του</i><i> 1899</i>, Λευκωσία, 1900. 
<p>The Charter currently in force of the Orthodox Church of Cyprus was published in the official journal of the Church Apostolos Varnavas, as well as in a special publication in 2010. Previous Charters had been published in 1979, 1929 (however, it never entered into force) and 1914 (a Procedure of the Ecclesiastical Courts was enacted in 1917). The Regulations of the Armenian Diocese of Cyprus were published in Nicosia in 1950. 
<p>The following publications cover the Laws of Vakf property: 
