<p><b>B. Case - Law Reports</b><b></b>
<p><b></b>
<p>The Judgments of the Supreme Court of Cyprus have been officially collected in the <b>Cyprus Law Reports </b>(CLR). Cases decided before Independence (1883-1960) were published in 24 volumes from 1893 until 1960. Cases decided after Independence have been collected in yearly volumes, with Part 1 (published since 1960) referring to Civil Cases, Part 2 (published since 1960) to Criminal Cases and Part 3 (published since 1965) to Administrative Cases. In 1964 only one volume was published comprising both Part 1 and Part 2. 
<p>Before 1989 the Cyprus Law Reports were published in English, while since 1989 they have been published in Greek as <b>Αποφάσεις</b><b> </b><b>Ανωτάτου</b><b> </b><b>Δικαστηρίου</b><b> </b>(ΑΑΔ). Since 1991 Part 1 further contains the Judgments of the Appeal Family Court. The Editors of the Cyprus Law Reports have been Markides Frixos (1961-1974), Kallis Panayiotis (1975-1985), Markides A. Hermione, Markides F. Alekos (1985-1990), Andreas Ladas (1991-1994, Part 1), Marios Kyriakides (1995-1996, Part 1), Papathoma-Kalligerou Marika (1991-1992, Part 3), Michaelidou Marietta (1991 onwards for Part 2, 1993 onwards for Part 3, 1997 onwards for Part 1). 
<p>All the judgments of the Supreme Constitutional Court of Cyprus have been collected in the <b>Reports of the Supreme Constitutional Court of Cyprus</b> from 1960-1963 in 5 volumes. The Editor was Fisentzides Chris. 
<p>From 1965-1987 the Judgments of the Supreme Court of Cyprus, as well as certain important judgments of the District Courts were published monthly in <b>Judgments of the Supreme Court of Cyprus</b> on Appeal and in its Original Jurisdiction and in Certain Cases Decided by District Courts in which there was no Appeal (JSC). The Editors were Constantinides Theodoros (1965-1968), Kallis Panayiotis (1969-1974), Markides A. Hermione, Markides F. Alekos, (1975-1987). From 1993-2005 Kyriakides Marios had been publishing monthly the Judgments of the Supreme Court and selected Judgments of District Courts in <b>Αποφάσεις</b><b> </b><b>Κυπριακών</b><b> </b><b>Δικαστηρίων</b> (ΑΚΔ). 
<p><i></i>
<p>A comprehensive and constantly updated website containing all Supreme Court Judgments, as well as recent District Court Judgments is <a href="http://www.leginet.eu/">www.leginet.eu</a>. Supreme Court Judgments are also included in the constantly updated website <a href="http://www.cylaw.org/">www.cylaw.org</a> which is free to the public. 
<p>Zekia Mehmet published a <i>Cyprus Law Reports Digest of Cases Reporter in Volumes I to XX</i> of the Cyprus Law Reports, which were decided before Independence. Constantinides Rogiros compiled a subsequent <i>Cyprus</i><i> Law Reports: Digest of Cases Containing Civil and Criminal Cases, Decided in the Years 1956 – 1971</i>. Denktash R. Rauf compiled <i>A Handbook of Criminal Cases</i>, Nicosia, 1955 which contained judgments decided before Independence. Cacoyiannis P. George published three volumes of collected cases in his <i>Cyprus Casebook</i>, v. I (1888-1969), Limassol 1978, v. 2 (1970-1977), Limassol, 1980, v. III (Index), Limassol, 1989 (Pattichis Elena had previously published an <i>Index to Cyprus Casebook by Cacoyiannis</i>, Limassol, 1981). Nikos Charalambous compiled a casebook of public law judgments for the year 1990 in Χαραλάμπους Νίκος, <i>Δελτίο</i><i> </i><i>Νομολογίας</i>, Εκδόσεις Ινστιτούτου Συνταγματικού και Διοικητικού Δικαίου, Λευκωσία, 1990.
<p>A collection of Judgments concerning Family Law have been published by Liassides Soteris in 2006 (Λιασίδης Σωτήρης, <i>Οικογενειακό</i><i> </i><i>Δίκαιο</i><i>: </i><i>Αποφάσεις</i>, τ. ΙΙα, Λευκωσία, 2006) and updated with new judgments from 2006-2010 in 2011 (<i>Οικογενειακό</i><i> </i><i>Δίκαιο</i><i>: </i><i>Αποφάσεις</i><i> 2006-2010</i>, τ. ΙΙβ, Λευκωσία, 2011). 
<p>27 volumes containing Decisions of the Industrial Relations Tribunal had been published as <i>Δικαστήριο</i><i> </i><i>Εργατικών</i><i> </i><i>Διαφορών</i><i>: </i><i>Αποφάσεις</i>. Volumes 1-5 were published as <i>Διαιτητικόν Δικαστήριον: Εκθέσεις Αποφάσεων του Διαιτητικού Δικαστηρίου</i>. Editors were Pisiaras Rovertos (v. 1-19) and Raspopoulos Savvas (v. 20-27). The Cyprus Employers and Industrialists Federations has published a collection of judgments of the Industrial Relations Tribunal in 1996 as Ομοσπονδία Εργοδοτών και Βιομηχάνων, <i>Αποφάσεις</i><i> </i><i>Δικαστηρίου</i><i> </i><i>Εργατικών</i><i> </i><i>Διαφορών</i>, Λευκωσία, 1996.
<p>Judgments of the Rent Control Tribunal have been collected in 9 volumes. The first eight volumes were edited by Coucounis Andreas as Κουκούνης Ανδρέας, <i>Ενοικιοστάσιο</i>, τ. Α΄ - Η΄, 1986 - 2003, Λευκωσία - Λάρνακα. The ninth volume, edited by Andreas Coucounis &amp; Co, was published in Larnaca in 2005 and contains the judgments from 2000-2004. 
<p>Judgments referring to Tax Law were compiled by Savvides Savvas, <i>Reports of Cyprus Tax Cases</i>, v. I – VIII, Institute of Certified Public Accountants of Cyprus, 1995 and by Νεοφύτου Νεόφυτος, <i>Συνοπτικός</i><i> </i><i>Οδηγός</i><i> </i><i>Αποφάσεων</i><i> </i><i>Δικαστηρίου</i><i> </i><i>Φορολογικών</i><i> </i><i>Υποθέσεων</i>, τ. Α: <i>Ο</i><i> </i><i>περί</i><i> </i><i>Φορολογίας</i><i> </i><i>του</i><i> </i><i>Εισοδήματος</i><i> </i><i>Νόμος</i>, Λευκωσία, 2003, τ. Β΄: <i>Ο</i><i> </i><i>περί</i><i> </i><i>Βεβαιώσεως</i><i> </i><i>και</i><i> </i><i>Εισπράξεως</i><i> </i><i>Φόρων</i><i> </i><i>Νόμος</i>, Λευκωσία, 2003, τ. Γ΄: <i>Ο</i><i> </i><i>περί</i><i> </i><i>Φορολογίας</i><i> </i><i>Κεφαλαιουχικών</i><i> </i><i>Κερδών</i><i> </i><i>Νόμος</i><i> </i><i>και</i><i> </i><i>Άλλοι</i><i> </i><i>Νόμοι</i>, Λευκωσία, 2003.
