<p>An Index to Treaties in Force was compiled by the Office of the Law Commissioner of the Republic of Cyprus, <i>Index of Treaties: 1960 - 2005</i>, Nicosia, 2006, pp. 510. The Republic had previously published an <i>Index to the Treaties and their Status</i>, Nicosia, 1986 and Supplement (1986 – 1991). Mavrommatis Andreas and Yiangou Christophoros had previously edited <i>A List of Treaties of the Republic of Cyprus in Force on the 1st January 1974</i>, Nicosia, 1974, pp. 35.
<p>The Cyprus and European Law Review has published an Index to issues 1-12 in (2011) 12 Cyprus and European Law Review. The Cyprus Law Review published an Index to its volumes for the years 1983-1987 as follows: Επιθεώρηση Κυπριακού Δικαίου, <i>Ευρετήριο</i><i> </i><i>Τόμων</i><i> 1983 – 1987</i>, Εκδόσεις Ασσέλια, Λευκωσία. The Cyprus Law Tribune published an index to its first nine years as follows: Κληρίδης Κώστας, <i>Κυπριακόν</i><i> </i><i>Νομικόν</i><i> </i><i>Βήμα</i><i>: </i><i>Ευρετήριο</i><i> </i><i>Έτη</i><i> </i><i>Α΄</i><i> - </i><i>Θ΄</i>.
<p><b>D</b><b>. Cypriot</b><b> Legal</b><b> Journals</b><b></b>
<p>The official journal of the Cyprus Bar Association, the <b>Cyprus Law Tribune</b> (Κυπριακό Νομικό Βήμα) was first founded in 1967 by Clerides Lefkos, then Chairman of the Cyprus Bar Association. The Tribune was initially being published every two months. In 1981 the publication of the Tribune was discontinued. The Tribune was published again from 1988 - 1995 and from 2000 onwards with the Chairman of the Cyprus Bar Association acting also as Editor of the Tribune. The Tribune is currently published thrice a year. The following have been Editors of the Tribune: Clerides Lefkos (1967-1981), Papaphilippou Loukis (1988-1993), Xenopoulos Xenios (1993-1995), Papaefstathiou Nicos (2000-2006), Ioannides Theodoros (2006 onwards). 
<p>The <b>Cyprus and European Law Review</b> (Επιθεώρηση Κυπριακού και Ευρωπαϊκού Δικαίου) was founded in 2006 by Emilianides C. Achilles, who continues to be the Editor of the Review. From 2006-2010 the Review was published three times a year by Dikaionomia Legal Publications, while from 2011 onwards the Review is published by . From 2009 onwards the Review is published under the scientific direction of the Law Department of the University of Nicosia. 12 issues of the Review have so far been published. The Review is a peer-reviewed journal. 
<p>The <b>Cyprus Law Review</b> (Επιθεώρησις Κυπριακού Δικαίου) was founded in 1983 as a quarterly publication published by Asselia Publications, with Nicolaou Eliana and Nicos Koutsou acting as Editors until 1996 when the publication was discontinued. The following volumes of the Review were published: 1 - 44, 49 - 50, 53 – 56.
<p><b>Lysias</b> (Λυσίας) is the official journal of the Nicosia Bar Association. Lysias was founded in 1994 and published without regularity until 2006. From 2008 onwards the journal is published by Nomiki Vivliothiki Publications of Athens with Nikitas Hadjimichael, Assistant Professor of the University of Cyprus, being the Editor. Two issues of the journal have so far been published under its new direction. 
<p>The <b>Family Law Review</b> (Επιθεώρηση Οικογενειακού Δικαίου) was launched in 2010 as a quarterly publication, with Judge Liasides Sotiris as the Editor. 
<p><b>Legal &amp; More</b> was launched in 2009 as a quarterly magazine with Georghiou Elena, a Cypriot lawyer from Larnaca, acting as Editor. 
<p>A short-lived publication was the <b>Review of Public and Private Law</b> (Επιθεώρησις Δημοσίου και Ιδιωτικού Δικαίου). The Review was published quarterly in 1967 in Nicosia with four issues being published in total. Ioannis Daskalakis was the Editor of the Review. </p>
